      "notes": "Sefton Asylum is a first-person horror game set in a 1960s psychiatric hospital. Players should be aware of the following mature content:\r\n\r\nViolence & Horror:\r\nThe game features psychological horror, implied medical violence, and disturbing imagery. Players will encounter references to unethical medical experiments performed on patients, including reanimation of the dead. While the game favors dread and suggestion over explicit gore, some clinical documents describe procedures and their effects in detached, medical language. Creatures roam the hospital at night and can attack the player.\r\n\r\nSensitive Mental Health Themes:\r\nThe game depicts psychiatric patients suffering from various conditions in a 1960s institutional setting. Historical treatments portrayed include electroconvulsive therapy, heavy sedation, and lobotomy. Patients are portrayed as victims of an outdated and cruel system, not as threats. Some patients exhibit self-harm behaviors or express distress.\r\n\r\nOther Sensitive Content:\r\nThe game explores themes of institutional abuse, medical malpractice, involuntary confinement, and the exploitation of vulnerable individuals by authority figures. A central storyline involves a family member being held captive and subjected to experimentation. The game contains no sexual content, no drug or alcohol abuse depictions, and no strong language."
